  "text": "Image acquisition was performed on a Philips Achieva 3.0-T scanner (Philips Medical Systems, Best, the Netherlands). Functional images were obtained using a 3-D PRESTO-SENSE pulse sequence [CITATION_1] with shimmed background and the following parameters: repetition time = 22.5 msec, echo time = 33.2 msec, flip angle = 10°, field of view = 224 × 256 × 160, matrix = 56 × 64 × 40, voxel size = 4 mm isotropic, scan time = 0.6075 sec, 40 slices (sagittal orientation). A total of 900 functional images were acquired. Immediately after the PMT task, one volume with a flip angle of 27°was acquired for image coregistration. A T1-weighted structural image was obtained for anatomical registration with the following parameters: repetition time = 9.5 msec, echo time = 4.7 msec, flip angle = 8°, field of view = 220.8 × 240 × 159.6, matrix = 368 × 400 × 266, voxel size = 0.6 mm isotropic, 266 slices (sagittal orientation).",
